Class LogfileReader

java.lang.Object
LogfileReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<LogEntry>
public class LogfileReader extends Object implements Iterator<LogEntry>
A class to read information from a file of web server accesses. Currently, the log file is assumed to contain simply date and time information in the format: year month day hour minute Log entries are sorted into ascending order of date.
Version:
2024.03.18
Author:
Andrew Steidle
